Commentary: sensational running catch from Thisara! He is at mid-on as the ball sails over his head, looking to break through the stratosphere, but he knows it is horribly timed. His momentum means he's almost at the wide long-on boundary, and is about to usher the ball over it. So he hits the brakes, changes direction and runs over to celebrate with a band of grateful team-mates

Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: short ball! Pitches outside off, and soars over Nawaz's head
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: back of a length just outside off, Nawaz ducks under the ball's line this time. Looks at the keeper for the wide. But not given
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: short and wide outside off, Sarfraz judges the length early, and caresses this cut past point! Third man dives across the ground but can't parry it back
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Sarfraz Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on off stump, Sarfraz shuffles across to the off side, and flicks towards square leg
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on middle, tries to punch towards midwicket, but comes off the bat's top half. In the air, but falls just of Sammy
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: short just outside off, flies off the surface and way over Safraz's head. Akmal has to go airborne to try and stop it. Does well in the end
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 wide

Commentary: good length just outside off, Sarfraz covers his off-stump line, and defends off the back foot
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Sarfraz Ahmed, no run

Commentary: full just outside off, opens the bat's face and taps to short third man. Calls early for the quick single, and comfortably completed
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: ends with a four! Good length on leg stump, and whipped off his hips this time. Lifted over square leg, and no one's there in the deep
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Mohammad Nawaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length on middle stump, Sarfraz goes deep onto the back foot, and punches this over the non-striker's head. In the air for ages, but just short of long on
Commentary_short: Dawson to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, angling across Nawaz, and cut to point. Too close to his body, so doesn't find the direction behind that shot
Commentary_short: Dawson to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: good length just outside off, slapped off the back foot past point. Work for the man whose at third man
Commentary_short: Dawson to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle stump. Tapped with soft hands towards point and they're off for a quick run. Swift pick-up from Fletcher, but chooses not to aim at the stumps. No one backing for that throw
Commentary_short: Dawson to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: full on off stump, and slashed hard at it. Muscled away to deep backward square
Commentary_short: Dawson to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, and Sarfraz comes charging down the wicket. Punched off the back foot to long off. He'll keep strike
Commentary_short: Dawson to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, can't flick it off his bat. Takes the back of his pad, and runs down to fine leg
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 leg bye

Commentary: good length on off stump, cramped Nawaz slightly. Blocked off the back foot to Wahab
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: full on leg stump, and it's been clipped uppishly over square leg. Checked his shot there, and that probably saves Nawaz. Drops just short of the man in the deep
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: full on off stump, angling across the batsman, and it's been crunched past cover. Work for the man in the deep, who races across to his right and stops the four
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Sarfraz Ahmed, 2 runs

Commentary: top edged! But falls in no man's land. Short on middle stump, but he's through his pull too early. Takes the bat's top-half, and falls safe
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, Nawaz tries to defend but takes the outside edge. Flies past the keeper's left and races across the ground. Goes to the third-man boundary in a flash!
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Mohammad Nawaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: tossed up on middle stump, and Safraz has deposited that into cow corner! Shimmies down the wicket, and lifts it over midwicket. Falls ten feet beyond the boundary
Commentary_short: Dawson to Sarfraz Ahmed, SIX runs

Commentary: use his feet once again! Good length on middle stump, but Sarfraz dances down the wicket. Muscled to wide long-on this time
Commentary_short: Dawson to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: good length on leg stump, grips the surface and turns into the left hander. Shuffles across to the leg side and nudges it to square leg
Commentary_short: Dawson to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle and leg, tapped off the front foot to midwicket. No one there, so the batsmen take the run. Work for Dawson, who has to do the fielder
Commentary_short: Dawson to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, backs away and cuts along the ground to deep point
Commentary_short: Dawson to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: smacked over Dawson's head! Lands over the sightscreen. Full on off stump, and Sarfraz uses his feet again. Dances down the wicket, and mistimes this straight drive. Still, enough behind that shot to take it beyond the ropes
Commentary_short: Dawson to Sarfraz Ahmed, SIX runs

Commentary: good length on leg stump, but Nawaz shuffles across to the off side. Can't flick it fine, but the ball goes down the leg side. More extras
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 wide

Commentary: good length just outside off, rocks onto the back foot, and punches to cover. No run this time
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: good length just outside off. Tries to cut but misses completely. Extra bounce, firstly, and then the ball was too close to Nawaz for the shot
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: good length outside off, slapped off the back foot to cover point. Man there
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: holes out! Taken at third man. Back of a length outside off and Nawaz comes down the ground. Tries to flat bat this over the bowler, but takes the bat's bottom edge. In the air for ages, allowing the outfielder to get under that catch. Peshawar needed a breakthrough and now they have it
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Mohammad Nawaz, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Nawaz c Umaid Asif b Sameen Gul 35 (32b 5x4 1x6) SR: 109.37

Commentary: two in two! And how things have turned. Sameen, you beauty. Both set batsmen have been sent back and this match has turned on its head! Short on middle stump, and Sarfraz tries to pull. The bat turns in his hands, and takes the top edge. It's a skier, and Kamran calls early for the catch. He ain't dropping that and Darren Sammy is pumped!
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Sarfraz Ahmed, OUT
Dismissal_text: Sarfraz Ahmed c †Kamran Akmal b Sameen Gul 35 (21b 3x4 2x6) SR: 166.66

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, tries to pull along the ground, but extra bounce once again. Hits his waist and goes to the keeper on the bounce
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Rossouw, no run

Commentary: full just outside off. Defended with the bat's open face. Sent to the vacant cover-region for a comfortable single
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Mahmudullah, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, tries to pull but the ball stays low! Bottom edged, and chopped down to fine leg
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Rossouw, 1 run

Commentary: full just outside off, tries to work it towards the leg side, the takes the leading edge. Flies over point, and runs away to the backward point boundary! What's that bat made off?
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Mahmudullah, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length outside off, but angling into the batsman. Tapped off the back foot to the bowler's right
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Mahmudullah, no run

Commentary: goes short this time. Keeps Mahmudullah wary. Pitches on off stump, and the batsman gets out of the ball's line very late. Umpire says, one for the over
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Mahmudullah, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, nudged off his pads to midwicket. Big 'no' called from the batsman
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Mahmudullah, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, punched with the bat's open face to point. They scamper across for the run
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Rossouw, 1 run

Commentary: good length outside off, the ball's angling into Mahmudullah. Opens the bat's face and runs this fine to third man
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Mahmudullah, 1 run

Commentary: good length just outside off, punched off the back foot to cover on this occasion. Keeping things tight
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Rossouw, no run

Commentary: lucky! Back of a length outside off, and Rossouw tries to pull. The ball stays low, and he bottom edges it onto his body. The ball ricochets away past the keeper's left thereafter, and Akmal's dive is futile as well. Races away behind the keeper for useful runs
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Rossouw, 4 leg byes

Commentary: good length, but wide outside off. Makes room to the leg side and bunted to mid off
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Rossouw, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, walks across to the off side and flicks to deep backward square for a comfortable single
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Mahmudullah, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, driven off the front foot to cover. Early call for the run, and easily done
Commentary_short: Dawson to Mahmudullah, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, bunted past the bowler's right on this occasion. Mistimes this down the ground to long off
Commentary_short: Dawson to Rossouw, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, backs away to make some extra room, and crunches this past cover! Deep extra cover can't cut it off, and neither can wide long off. Terrific shot from Mahmudullah. Used the full depth of the crease there
Commentary_short: Dawson to Mahmudullah, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length on middle stump, he walks down the wicket but is forced to change his shot. Fended towards the bowler, but takes the inside edge onto his pads
Commentary_short: Dawson to Mahmudullah, no run

Commentary: flat and short outside off, pulled off the back foot to deep midwicket. Lost his balance while playing that shot, Mahmudullah
Commentary_short: Dawson to Mahmudullah, 1 run

Commentary: good length outside off, makes room to the leg side and punches this to long off's right. Work for the man there
Commentary_short: Dawson to Rossouw, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on leg stump, slower ball to start off with, but the ball's too short. Loops over Rossouw's shoulder as he pulls out of the leg-side heave. The bowler's not pleased with that decision
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Rossouw, 1 wide

Commentary: yorker on leg stump. Squeezes it to the on side, and Umaid intercepts the shot on his follow through
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Rossouw, no run

Commentary: low full toss on middle stump, punched to mid off but for only a run. Rossouw's disappointed having missed out on that loose ball
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Rossouw, 1 run

Commentary: good length just outside off, Mahmudullah walks across to the off side and pokes at it. Andre Fletcher's sharp at backward point. Stopped in a flash
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Mahmudullah, no run

Commentary: big heave from the batsman, but through to the keeper. Good length on off stump, and he gave the bowler a charge. Tried to lift this towards the leg side, but the ball zips away from him after pitching. Nice carry through to Kamran
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Mahmudullah, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, and he slogs this over midwicket! Towards cow corner, and falls just short of the boundary. Stayed still this time, and whipped this from outside off stump. Rich vein of form continues
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Mahmudullah, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length outside off, tries to make room on the leg side and slap it over point, but can't make contact. Flies past the bat's top edge and through to the keeper
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Mahmudullah, no run

Commentary: good length outside off, punched off the back foot past cover point to the man in the deep
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Rossouw, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, soars over the batsman's shoulders
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Mahmudullah, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, tapped towards mid on for a quick single. Nobody there so Hasan has to scamper across to his right and stop that ball
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Mahmudullah, 1 run

Commentary: full outside off, and slightly slower this time. Rossouw tries to smack this over the bowler's head, but alas! Through his shot too early. Big wind up from the batsman on this occasion
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Rossouw, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, angling into Rossouw and gets slightly big on him. Punched away from his body past cover to the man in the deep
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Rossouw, 1 run

Commentary: good length just outside off. Keeps his bat's face open, and runs it down to third man for a walking single
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Mahmudullah, 1 run

Commentary: over the keeper's head and find leg can't intercept either! Good length on off, and he tries to pull it square. Can't connect and the ball takes his shoulder. The dive from the man in the deep was good, but not good enough!
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Mahmudullah, 4 leg byes

Commentary: breaks off stump! Full on off stump, and Mahmudullah tries to smack this over the bowler's head. He misses, and the bowler hits! Takes top of off stump. The batsman played down the wrong line there
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Mahmudullah, OUT

Commentary: full on leg stump, and checks his drive over the bowler's head. Long on's there, but the ball falls just short of the fielder. Chipped, really
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Perera, 1 run

Commentary: full outside off, tries to slash hard at it, but he's sliced it. In the air for ages, but Hasan Ali has all the time in the world for that. Takes a few steps in front  - from deep point - and takes a nice catch. The ball was swirling in the air, but the fielder stayed composed. Rossouw goes for a 14-ball 8
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Rossouw, OUT
Dismissal_text: RR Rossouw c Hasan Ali b Umaid Asif 8 (14b 0x4 0x6) SR: 57.14

Commentary: short on off stump, and he tries a big heave on the leg side. Can't make the connection, and the ball's taken by Akmal from over his head. This pitch still has a lot of life in it
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Perera, no run

Commentary: good length on leg stump, tries to whip it towards the leg side, but through his shot too early. Comes off his bat's shoulder and goes to short fine-leg's right. Well stopped by the fielder there! The ball took an awkward bounce, but sticks in his right hand. Definitely saved a sure boundary
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Perera, 1 run

Commentary: short and wide outside off, Perera tries to slap this over point, but the ball's taken the top edge! Flies over the keeper for a maximum! Width offered and punished.
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Perera, SIX runs

Commentary: low full toss on middle stump, mistimes his slog to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Perera, 1 run

Commentary: short on off stump, tries to ramp it over the keeper, but can't make the connection! Misses, and Wahab will happily take the dot. Could've easily gone for four, though
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Anwar Ali, no run

Commentary: almost a yorker on off stump. Can't get his bat under it this time. Can only push it towards mid off for a single
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Anwar Ali, 1 run

Commentary: low full toss on middle stump once again. Misses the yorker once more, but Thisara can't punish it. Mistimes his slog to deep midwicket once again
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Perera, 1 run

Commentary: full and straight this time. Muscled down the ground to long off for a walking single. Anwar keeps strike
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Anwar Ali, 1 run

Commentary: good length outside off, pokes at it and runs this down to third man
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Anwar Ali, 1 run

Commentary: good length outside off, but it's the cutter on this occasion. Perera tries to slog this over the leg side, but through the shot too early. Misses it completely
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Perera, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, but another slower ball! Perera tries to drive this inside out, but once again through his shot too early. Takes the bat's toe end and goes to Hasan
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Perera, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, muscles this pull down the ground. Goes to wide long on, and the throw from there is sent in in a flash! No chance of a second
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Perera, 1 run

Commentary: short on off stump, tries to pull this into the stands, but can only swivel. Can't connect as the ball goes over his bat. Only two off the over. How can Hasan Ali finish?
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Anwar Ali, no run

Commentary: another dot! What an over. Good length outside off, and tries another leg-side heave. Can't make the connect and Hasan finishes his spell in a terrific manner!
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Anwar Ali, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, squeezed to deep backward point but for only a single! Anwar's back on strike. Peshawar won't mind
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Perera, 1 run

Commentary: good length on leg stump, flat-batted over the bowler's head to long on. Perera's back on strike
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Anwar Ali, 1 run

Commentary: holes out to long on! Taken by Jordan, the sub. Full and wide outside off, and Perera drags his slog to the leg side. Straight to long on, and Jordan has to bend slightly down to complete the catch. Peshawar firmly on top now
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Perera, OUT
Dismissal_text: NLTC Perera c sub (CJ Jordan) b Wahab Riaz 12 (11b 0x4 1x6) SR: 109.09

Commentary: good length on off stump, bunted over Wahab to long on once again. Flat-bats it but not off the bat's middle
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Anwar Ali, 1 run

Commentary: edged! And that's the second wicket of the over. Good length on off stump, and Hasan tries to run this down fine. Gets bat on ball, but ends up edging it straight to Akmal. Quetta need 25 off 7
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Hassan Khan, OUT
Dismissal_text: Hassan Khan c †Kamran Akmal b Wahab Riaz 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: yorker on off stump. Bottom edged by the batsman but the ball goes nowhere. It's near his boots, and Wahab ends with a dot. Akmal runs across and hugs Wahab for that over
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Mir Hamza, no run

Commentary: full outside off, and Anwar takes a big swing at it. Takes the top edge, and falls past Sammy's left. He's hobbling across - at third man - but Dawson's not pleased at all
Commentary_short: Dawson to Anwar Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: ten off two! Quetta aren't going down just yet. Full outside off, and Anwar shimmies down the wicket. Meets it on the full, and muscled over long on. This game ain't over just yet
Commentary_short: Dawson to Anwar Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: full and wide outside off. Tries to drive this inside out over cover, but takes the inside edge. Goes to short fine leg, and refuses the single
Commentary_short: Dawson to Anwar Ali, no run

Commentary: lifted! Over long on. Flat ball outside off, and Anwar once again charges down the wicket to smack it to the leg side. Full follow through of the bat!
Commentary_short: Dawson to Anwar Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: over long off! This is unbelievable. Good length just outside off, Anwar comes down the wicket again and bunts it over Dawson's head. Tears in the stands among Peshawar fans
Commentary_short: Dawson to Anwar Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: Peshawar win by one! Full toss on middle stump, and it's been smacked over Dawson! Dropped at long on but he's quick to throw it back in. The batsmen try to take the second, but they can't make it. Dawson takes the bails off at the non-striker's and Quetta Gladiators are eliminated.
Commentary_short: Dawson to Anwar Ali, 1 run, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mir Hamza run out (Umaid Asif/Dawson) 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00
